---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import logData from "../data/log.json";

// Entries are generated every ~48h by ~/scripts/log-digest, which gathers real
// signals (git commits, Claude Code sessions, vault deltas, ChatGPT history),
// summarizes + sanitizes them through one Claude call, and writes log.json.
const entries = logData.entries;
---

<Layout title="log | MERULOX" description="A running log of what merulox is building and thinking.">
	<h1>Log</h1>

	<p class="log-note">
		A running record of what's moving — shipped work, shifts in focus, things
		learned. Eventually generated from the systems that already track this:
		writing, listening, commits, the vault. For now, a sketch.
	</p>

	<ul class="log-list">
		{
			entries.map((e) => (
				<li class="log-entry">
					<div class="log-meta">
						<time class="log-date">{e.date}</time>
						<span class="log-kind">{e.kind}</span>
					</div>
					<p class="log-text">{e.text}</p>
				</li>
			))
		}
	</ul>

	<!--
	IDEAS for the log (build later):

	- Auto-feed: pull recent git commits across active repos (Genesis, SYNTRA, this site),
	  filter to meaningful ones, render as dated entries.
	- Weekly scrobble digest: "this week: heavy $uicideboy$, first time hearing X" —
	  generated from Last.fm weekly chart deltas.
	- Writing pings: new Substack posts auto-append a log line linking the piece.
	- Vault signal: when a note crosses from inbox → permanent (synthesized), log it
	  as "learned: <claim>" — surfaces the knowledge graph growing without exposing it.
	- Reading movement: book status changes (get it → owned → read) become log lines.
	- Milestone markers: Boréal client #1, first $X MRR, Genesis embodiment step — manual
	  but high-signal, pinned above the auto-feed.
	- Format: group by month, reverse-chronological, monospace dates, one-line entries,
	  kind tag (ship / think / read / listen / learn). No metrics, no charts — keep it human.
	- Source of truth: a single log.json (or the obsidian daily notes) that a build step
	  compiles; site stays static.
	-->
</Layout>
